Your `add(int index, String value)` indexing logic is a bit confused:
* you insert at the head of the list when index is 0 or 1;
* in other cases your methods behave as if the list is indexed starting from 1, which is probably not intended;
* you insert before `current` element except if that `current` element is the last one, and in that case you insert after `current` element. Insertion should be consistent with regard to your index position in the list

Your `remove(int index)` has the same problem with mixing up index 0 and 1 and removing the head in both cases.

And be on the lookout for opportunities to improve your code and make it more concise, that usually also helps with debugging.

